      <div class="body">
        <span class="role-tag">Growing up in the Keys</span>
        <p>
          A six-mile stretch of islands in the Florida Keys is hard to leave but harder
          to take seriously as a base of operations. Growing up there meant the water was
          always close and the ceiling was always low &mdash; if you wanted somewhere bigger,
          you had to go find it.
        </p>
        <p>
          Sports filled most of the days that school didn&rsquo;t &mdash; soccer, baseball,
          basketball, tennis, ping pong, chess. The saxophone in middle and high school.
          The four years at Coral Shores High School ended as co-captain of the swim team,
          competing at the district and regional levels in the 200&nbsp;m freestyle and
          100&nbsp;m butterfly.
        </p>
        <div class="highlights">
          <div class="hi"><div class="k">Sports</div><div class="v">6+ <span class="unit">disciplines</span></div></div>
          <div class="hi"><div class="k">Swim team</div><div class="v">Co-captain</div></div>
