      <div class="body">
        <span class="role-tag">Florida State University · College of Business</span>
        <p>
          Four years at Florida State&rsquo;s College of Business, finishing in 2009
          with a B.S. in Finance and Real Estate. The classroom was half of it; the
          other half was Theta Chi &mdash; at the time, the fraternity with the highest
          overall GPA on campus, and the one that took its philanthropic work and
          intramural athletics seriously.
        </p>
        <p>
          Brotherhood Chairman for one year (running the annual retreat and internal
          programming), Athletic Chairman for two (assembling teams and coordinating
          participation across intramural sports). A lot of what came later &mdash;
          organizing people, sequencing work, keeping a group moving in the same
          direction &mdash; got its first rep here.
        </p>
        <div class="highlights">
          <div class="hi"><div class="k">Degree</div><div class="v">B.S. <span class="unit">Finance + Real Estate</span></div></div>
