      <div class="body">
        <span class="role-tag">U.S. Navy · Naval Special Warfare Development Group</span>
        <p>
          Enlisted in 2010 with the goal of becoming a SEAL. Made it through boot camp
          and several weeks of additional physical training, then was not selected to
          continue. Pivoted to the Intelligence Specialist rating and reported to the
          Navy and Marine Corps Intelligence Training Center in Dam&nbsp;Neck, Virginia,
          where the previous failure became the motivation &mdash; graduated at the top
          of the class in both general naval intelligence and the follow-on ground
          operations course.
        </p>
        <p>
          That earned an invitation to screen for an intelligence position with an
          elite special missions unit. After a week of psychological evaluations,
          physical and written tests, and a series of boards, joined Naval Special
          Warfare Development Group (NSWDG) in April&nbsp;2011.
        </p>
        <p>
          Over four overseas combat deployments, took on roles not typically assigned
          to Intelligence Specialists. As an <strong>Analyst</strong>, researched and
          aggregated intelligence to support special operations missions targeting
          high-value individuals. As an <strong>ISR Manager</strong>, coordinated the
          deployment of manned and unmanned ISR assets in excess of 10,000&nbsp;hours.
          Served as a <strong>Liaison Officer</strong> between the Central Intelligence
          Agency and the commander of NSWDG. Most notably, served as
          <strong>Joint Staff Intelligence Officer</strong> for a 70-person task force
          &mdash; a position normally reserved for military officers as the most senior
          intelligence role in the area of operations.
        </p>
        <p>
          Honorably discharged in January&nbsp;2016 at the rank of Petty Officer
          Second Class.
        </p>
        <div class="highlights">
          <div class="hi"><div class="k">Deployments</div><div class="v">04 <span class="unit">combat tours</span></div></div>
          <div class="hi"><div class="k">ISR coordinated</div><div class="v">10,000+ <span class="unit">hrs</span></div></div>
          <div class="hi"><div class="k">Task force</div><div class="v">70 <span class="unit">pax · JSIO</span></div></div>
          <div class="hi"><div class="k">Rank at EAS</div><div class="v">PO2 · IS2</div></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>

