      <div class="body">
        <span class="role-tag">Software engineering · ten years · engineer → lead → manager</span>
        <p>
          Started writing code as a hobby while still in the Navy. Building small
          websites turned into a strong-enough interest that engineering became the
          next career on purpose. First role was Junior PHP Developer at
          Partner&nbsp;Weekly &mdash; a marketing agency in the consumer specialty
          finance space &mdash; learning the fundamentals, attending and speaking at
          local PHP meetups, and contributing to open source.
        </p>
        <p>
          From there, Switch,&nbsp;Inc. &mdash; the data center company &mdash; for a
          long run that went Software Engineer → Manager of Software Engineering
          (2019) → Software Engineer III → Technical Project Manager. Built APIs and
          back-end systems supporting day-to-day operations, then a team of eight
          building them. The most lasting contribution was an automated CI/CD
          pipeline that became how the engineering org shipped.
        </p>
        <p>
          Joined Guidepoint Global in April&nbsp;2023 as Lead Software Engineer,
          architecting a company-wide migration to containerized, cloud-native
          workflows across 10+ teams and 20+ services on Azure Kubernetes Service.
          Promoted to Software Engineering Manager in 2025, leading two teams (11
          direct reports) delivering AI-powered features. Promoted again in
          January&nbsp;2026 to <strong>Senior Software Engineering Manager</strong>,
          leading architecture and delivery for Guidepoint&rsquo;s next-generation
          agentic platform &mdash; defining MCP-based tooling, integration patterns
          with the core CRM, and the reliability and auth models that production
          agentic systems demand.
        </p>
        <p>
          UNLV Executive&nbsp;MBA in 2022 along the way. Climbing rock for the last
          stretch of it, on whatever weekends will allow.
        </p>
